core.conflict

Class AbstractConflictResolutionStrategy<T,E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • core.conflict.AbstractConflictResolutionStrategy<T,E>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of entities that define the conflict scope of this conflict resolution strategy.
    E - The type of entities that underly the conflict incurred by the conflict source entity resolved by this conflict resolution strategy.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IConflictResolutionStrategy<T,E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractRenameConflictResolutionStrategy, DiscardConflictResolutionStrategy

    public abstract class AbstractConflictResolutionStrategy<T,E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements IConflictResolutionStrategy<T,E>
    an AbstractConflictResolutionStrategy generic abstract class that is used to factor the common interface and state of all concrete conflict resolution strategy classes.

    It must be specialized by all concrete conflict resolution strategy classes.
    Author:
    Bachar Rima
    See Also:
    AbstractConflictScope, AbstractConflictSource

      Constructors

      AbstractConflictResolutionStrategy(T target, AbstractConflictScope<T,E> conflictScope, boolean sameSemantics)
      Creates a conflict resolution strategy having target as its target, conflictScope as its conflict scope and sameSemantics to indicate whether the pre/post transformation elements of the conflict source of its conflict scope share the same semantics
